Package: mixLCA
Type: Package
Title: Partitioned Latent Class Analysis with Local Dependence and Distal Outcomes
Version: 1.0.1
Authors@R: person("Ali Sanaei", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                   email = "sanaei@uchicago.edu")
Description: Finite mixture modelling with a partitioned architecture that
    enforces temporal separation between antecedent predictors, contemporaneous
    manifest indicators, and subsequent distal outcomes. Class membership
    probabilities depend on concomitant predictors via multinomial logistic
    regression. Continuous indicators follow class-specific multivariate
    normal distributions with optional non-diagonal covariance (local
    dependence) and L1-penalised sparsity estimation. Missing continuous
    data is handled through analytical marginalisation. Distal outcomes are
    estimated under BCH inverse-classification-error weighting, preventing
    construct contamination. Provides information criteria, bivariate
    residual diagnostics, profile plots, and network visualisations.
